Done. Built **mdcheck** - a zero-dependency markdown link checker CLI:

```
/workspace
├── bin/mdcheck.js    # CLI entrypoint
├── lib/
│   ├── checker.js    # Link extraction & validation
│   └── glob.js       # Glob pattern matching
├── test.js           # Unit tests (3 passing)
├── example.md        # Demo file
└── package.json
```

**Features:**
- Extracts `[text](url)` links from markdown
- Concurrent HTTP HEAD requests with fallback to GET
- Glob pattern support (`docs/**/*.md`)
- Configurable timeout & concurrency
- Shows broken links only (or all with `-v`)

**Usage:** `node bin/mdcheck.js README.md` or `npm link` to install globally.
